This project uses components from the Python standard library,
licensed under the Python Software Foundation License (PSF License):
https://docs.python.org/3/license.html

- __future__ - future feature imports

- sys - interpreter and runtime
- os - file system and environment
- re - regular expression matching operations
- shutil - directory operations like copying, moving, and deleting

- time - timing and sleep utilities
- datetime - date and time objects
- collections - high-performance container datatypes
- typing - type hints (Any, TextIO)

- builtins - implicit base types
- gc - garbage collector interface
- tempfile - temporary files and directories
- unittest.mock - testing and mocking utilities

- csv - CSV parsing and writing
- json - JSON serialization
- winsound - playing sounds and beeps (Windows-only module)

- sqlite3 - included with Python under the PSF License;
  the underlying SQLite engine is in the Public Domain:
  https://sqlite.org/copyright.html
  (Released into the public domain by D. Richard Hipp)

